cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DS

Reasoning: The paper deals with the downlink of large wireless networks and analyzes the achievable sum-rate as a function of various network parameters. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also proposes design guidelines for regulators to guarantee QoS constraints and maximize revenue, which falls under the domain of control systems (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the comparison between low-powered peer-to-peer networks and high-powered single-transmitter networks, which falls under the domain of multimedia (cs.MM) and distributed systems (cs.DS).
